@node "Overview" "Overview"
@wordwrap
@tab 25
@font "CGTimes.font" 18



@{jcenter}@{u}Overview@{uu}



@{jleft}-For years on the classic Amiga, I used a speech clock called VClock (Author: Allan Versaevel) which is available on Aminet.  This program was very useful since I would lose track of time while programming, playing games, using paint programs, fine tuning my workbench, etc.  That program would remind me of the time while I was working, so I would not lose track of time.

@{jleft}-Now that we are using the Next Generation Amiga (AmigaOne), that program is no longer compatible, but the need for a speaking clock was still there, hence ChronoVox was born.

@{jleft}-ChronoVox is a program that announce the time on the half and full hour of everyday.  It runs in the background and uses very little resources.





@endnode
@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@font "CGTimes.font" 18
@wordwrap
@tab 25

@{jcenter}@{u}Requirements@{uu}

@{jleft}1.) AmigaOne 500, AmigaOne X1000 (OS 4.1.1 or better)
@{jleft}2.) SoundPlayer V53.0 or better (Include With OS 4.1.1 in C: Directory)


@{jcenter}@{b}@{u}Note@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}-Not tested with Micro AmigaOne, AmigaOne SE, AmigaOne XE, Pegasus 2, Amiga 1200/4000 (PPC).  ChronoVox should work with these systems also.









@endnode
@node "Installation" "Installation"
@font "CGTimes.font" 18
@wordwrap
@tab 25

@{jcenter}@{u}Installation@{uu}

@{jleft}-Simply unpacked it anywhere you want.  


@{jcenter}@{b}@{u}NOTE@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}-The Sound directory MUST be in the same drawer containing the ChronoVox program.  It is recommended that you keep the ChronoVox directory intact and copy it anywhere you would like on your AmigaOne.



  








@endnode
@node "Usage" "Usage"
@font "CGTimes.font" 18
@wordwrap
@tab 25

@{jcenter}@{u}Usage@{uu}

@{jleft}-ChronoVox can be started by either clicking on it's icon or by adding it to your Wbstartup which will start it at boot.

@{jleft}-Controlling ChronoVox is done using the Exchange program found in the System: drive in the Utilities/Commodities drawer. In Exchange you can pause ChronoVox by using the Inactive or Active tab, and you can quit the program by selecting the Remove tab.


@{jcenter}@{b}@{u}NOTE@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}-ChronoVox cannot be started from the Shell/CLI.

@{jleft}-ChronoVox cannot be run more that once.  If it is already running and you try to run it again, it will give an error message.







@endnode
